},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Double","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"title":"ratio","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The computed contrast ratio between two given colors"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://OUDSFoundations/documentation/OUDSFoundations/OUDSWCAG21Ratio":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSFoundations\/documentation\/OUDSFoundations\/OUDSWCAG21Ratio","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Some countries set up new laws so as to force companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is for example the case for France with the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also named “RGAA”."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is higly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for textual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This utility helps to define wether a set of contrast ratio matches AA and AAA or not."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"See for example "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/system.design.orange.com\/0c1af118d\/p\/2531b9-accessibility-compliance"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio"}],"title":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio","url":"\/documentation\/oudsfoundation